  (b) **Repackage as Services**: use the Materials, in whole or in part, as the operational substance, methodology, or backbone of consulting, advisory, training, audit, assessment, or other services provided by Licensee to third parties;

  (c) **Sublicense** the Materials or any rights granted under this Agreement to any third party;

  (d) **White-label or Rebrand** the Materials or any Derivative Work, by removing or obscuring AI Enablement OS™ branding, attribution, or license metadata, or by presenting the Materials as the work product of Licensee or any third party;

  (e) **Create Derivative Works for Distribution**: create, prepare, or distribute Derivative Works of the Materials for any purpose other than Internal Organisational Use;

  (f) **Remove or Alter Notices**: remove, alter, obscure, or circumvent any copyright notice, license metadata field (including the `license:` and `licensee:` fields embedded in skill file YAML frontmatter), trademark notice, attribution, or licensee identifier in or accompanying the Materials;

  (g) **Train Models**: use the Materials, or any portion or Derivative Work thereof, to train, fine-tune, or otherwise improve any machine learning model, foundation model, or AI system that is offered, distributed, or made available to any party other than the Licensee for the Licensee's Internal Organisational Use;

  (h) **Reverse Engineer Licensee Identifiers**: attempt to remove, obfuscate, or render undetectable any licensee-specific identifier, watermark, or fingerprint embedded in the Materials delivered to Licensee;

  (i) **Circumvent License Verification**: bypass, disable, or interfere with any technical or procedural measure intended to verify license compliance.

